@startuml Report Assignment Flow
title Demo App Flow: Assigning Reports to Users/Roles

actor "Data Owner\n(Admin)" as Admin
participant "Library UI" as UI
participant "SavedReportController" as Controller
database "Database" as DB

== Opening the Assignment Modal ==
Admin -> UI : Open "Saved Reports"
activate UI
UI -> Controller : GET /reports
activate Controller
Controller -> DB : Select all SavedReports\nwith assignedUsers
activate DB
DB --> Controller : SavedReports Collection
deactivate DB
Controller --> UI : Render View
deactivate Controller

Admin -> UI : Click "Assign" on a Report
UI -> UI : Open Assignment Modal
UI -> UI : Fetch all Users & Roles (via API/State)
UI --> Admin : Display Multi-Select Users/Roles

== Saving Assignments ==
Admin -> UI : Select Users (e.g., 'analyst@istore.com')
Admin -> UI : Click "Save Assignments"
UI -> Controller : POST /reports/{id}/assign\n(user_ids array)
activate Controller

Controller -> DB : Find SavedReport by ID
activate DB
DB --> Controller : SavedReport Instance
deactivate DB

Controller -> DB : sync() dynamic_report_user pivot
activate DB
note right: Laravel Eloquent automatically inserts/deletes\nrecords in the many-to-many pivot table.
DB --> Controller : Success
deactivate DB

Controller --> UI : Redirect / Success Message
deactivate Controller

UI --> Admin : Show "Assigned Successfully" Alert
deactivate UI

@enduml
